.TH F00-TAIL 1 "2026" "f00 0.15.0-beta.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
f00\-tail \- output the last part of files (f00 suite)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B f00\-tail
[\fIOPTION\fR]... [\fIFILE\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Print the last 10 lines of each FILE to standard output.
With more than one FILE, precede each with a header.
Pure assembly multicall. MIT.
.PP
Default is modern mode.
.B \-\-core
selects strict GNU tail\-compatible output.
.SH COREUTILS FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-lines\fR=\fIN\fR
output the last N lines
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-bytes\fR=\fIN\fR
output the last N bytes
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-follow\fR
output appended data as the file grows
.TP
\fB\-q\fR / \fB\-v\fR
never / always print headers
.PP
See
.B f00\-tail \-\-help
for the full flag list.
.SH MODERN FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-\-core\fR
strict coreutils\-compatible output
.TP
\fB\-j\fR, \fB\-\-json\fR
JSON summary when supported
.TP
\fB\-\-csv\fR
CSV summary when supported
.SH AUTHOR
f00 contributors. License MIT.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tail (1),
.BR f00\-head (1),
.BR f00 (1)
.PP
https://f00.sh
